<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-10-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-10-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="499" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d499">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Messrs. <persName type="from">Parson &amp;
                                        French</persName>, attorneys for the United States, to Mr.
                                        <persName type="to">Hoar</persName>, Attorney-General.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilmington, North
                                        Carolina</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-10-09"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 9,
                                1869</date>.</dateline>
                            <p rend="flushleft">Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">E. R. Hoar</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Attorney-General:</hi></p>
                            <p>District attorney is not here. There is no telegraph. Mr. Hall should
                                be here, we think.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>PARSON &amp; FRENCH.</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>